Mr Johnson called Mr Starmer a"pointless plastic bollard you see around a deserted motorway".MPs will take part in a vote that will whittle down the Tory leadership hopefuls to just two between 1pm and 3pm this afternoon and the results will be announced by chair of the 1922 committee Sir Graham Brady at 4pm. Mr Johnson was forced to resign last month after a number of cabinet ministers stepped down from their positions, having lost confidence in his leadership. His successor will be announced on September 5 and will aim to bring change to a party that has been rocked by a number of high-profile scandals. THIS BLOG IS NOW CLOSED 